  "prompt": "What are the works to be carried out as an assistant executive officer in mechanical department in ONGC?",
  "response": "As an Assistant Executive Officer (AEO) in the Mechanical Department of Oil and Natural Gas Corporation (ONGC), your responsibilities would typically include:\n\n1. Technical Support:\n- Assist in maintenance planning of mechanical equipment\n- Support technical evaluation of machinery and equipment\n- Collaborate in preparing technical reports and documentation\n- Help in equipment inspection and condition monitoring\n\n2. Operational Tasks:\n- Coordinate mechanical maintenance activities\n- Monitor equipment performance and efficiency\n- Support preventive and predictive maintenance schedules\n- Assist in troubleshooting mechanical systems\n\n3. Project Management:\n- Support mechanical engineering projects\n- Help in project planning and implementation\n- Assist in project cost estimation and tracking\n- Coordinate with different teams and departments\n\n4. Safety and Compliance:\n- Ensure compliance with safety standards\n- Implement safety protocols in mechanical operations\n- Conduct safety inspections and risk assessments\n- Maintain equipment safety records\n\n5. Administrative Responsibilities:\n- Prepare reports and presentations\n- Manage documentation and records\n- Support procurement processes\n- Assist in budget preparations\n\n6. Technical Analysis:\n- Analyze mechanical performance data\n- Support technical investigations\n- Contribute to improvement recommendations\n- Assist in developing technical strategies\n\nThese responsibilities may vary based on specific ONGC requirements and departmental needs.",
